[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":927},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2020\u002F02\u002F14\u002Fone-command-deploy-vue-cli-to-github-pages\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2020\u002F02\u002F14\u002Fone-command-deploy-vue-cli-to-github-pages\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2020\u002F02\u002F14\u002Fone-command-deploy-vue-cli-to-github-pages\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2020\u002F02\u002F14\u002Fone-command-deploy-vue-cli-to-github-pages\u002F":904,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2020\u002F02\u002F14\u002Fone-command-deploy-vue-cli-to-github-pages\u002F":913},"\u002Fvue\u002F20200214\u002F1055437216\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":887,"date":888,"description":19,"extension":889,"lang":890,"meta":891,"navigation":52,"path":892,"readingMinutes":893,"seo":894,"standalone":895,"stem":896,"tags":897,"tldr":901,"updated":888,"url":902,"__hash__":903},"content\u002Fen\u002FVue\u002Fone-command-deploy-vue-cli-to-github-pages.md","One-Command Deploy: Vue CLI to GitHub Pages","2130154657",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":877},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,35,44,53,57,90,97,320,323,334,337,344,353,356,362,366,371,375,384,390,394,400,403,414,419,720,726,737,740,744,747,829,832,855,861,865,873],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"When you finish a Vue CLI project, you usually want to deploy it somewhere so people can see it — GitHub Pages being one option. This post walks through how to deploy it in a single command.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"example-project","Example project",[17,25,26,27,34],{},"I'll be using one of my older API-integration projects as the example — \"",[28,29,33],"a",{"href":30,"rel":31},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002FHexfootMusic",[32],"nofollow","Hexfoot Music","\".",[17,36,37,38,43],{},"This was a sample project I introduced during a ",[28,39,42],{"href":40,"rel":41},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.hexschool.com\u002F",[32],"Hexschool"," online Q&A session. If you're curious about the KKBOX OPEN API, here's the YouTube video for reference:",[45,46],"iframe",{"width":47,"height":48,"src":49,"frameBorder":50,"allow":51,"allowFullScreen":52},560,315,"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.youtube.com\u002Fembed\u002FaVVLs2mlf8k","0","accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture",true,[12,54,56],{"id":55},"one-command-deploy-basics","One-command deploy basics",[17,58,59,60,64,65,68,69,72,73,76,77,81,82,84,85,89],{},"Normally before deploying a project you'd run ",[61,62,63],"code",{},"npm run build",", which spits out a ",[61,66,67],{},"dist"," folder. If you do it the manual way — ",[61,70,71],{},"cd dist",", ",[61,74,75],{},"git init",", and so on — it gets annoying after a few rounds. My earlier post ",[28,78,80],{"href":79},"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F13\u002Fdeploy-vuejs-to-github-pages\u002F","Deploying Vue.js to GitHub Pages"," actually walks through the manual approach. But during real dev you usually run ",[61,83,63],{}," over and over, so here's how to ",[86,87,88],"strong",{},"deploy to GitHub Pages with one command",".",[17,91,92,93,96],{},"First, create a file called ",[61,94,95],{},"deploy.sh"," in your project root with this content:",[98,99,104],"pre",{"className":100,"code":101,"language":102,"meta":103,"style":103},"language-sh shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","#!\u002Fusr\u002Fbin\u002Fenv sh\n\n# exit on error\nset -e\n\n# build\nnpm run build\n\n# move into the build folder — adjust if you changed the output dir\ncd dist\n\n# deploy to a custom domain\n# echo 'www.example.com' > CNAME\n\ngit init\ngit add -A\ngit commit -m 'deploy'\n\n# deploy to https:\u002F\u002F\u003CUSERNAME>.github.io\n# git push -f git@github.com:\u003CUSERNAME>\u002F\u003CUSERNAME>.github.io.git master\n\n# deploy to https:\u002F\u002F\u003CUSERNAME>.github.io\u002F\u003CREPO>\n# git push -f git@github.com:\u003CUSERNAME>\u002F\u003CREPO>.git master:gh-pages\n# for this project, change to the line below — this is the SSH version\ngit push -f git@github.com:hsiangfeng\u002FHexfootMusic.git master:gh-pages\n# you could also use HTTPS\n# git push -f https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002FHexfootMusic.git master:gh-pages\n\ncd -\n","sh","",[61,105,106,115,121,127,137,142,148,162,167,173,182,187,193,199,204,213,224,238,243,249,255,260,266,272,278,295,301,307,312],{"__ignoreMap":103},[107,108,111],"span",{"class":109,"line":110},"line",1,[107,112,114],{"class":113},"sQrFR","#!\u002Fusr\u002Fbin\u002Fenv sh\n",[107,116,118],{"class":109,"line":117},2,[107,119,120],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":52},"\n",[107,122,124],{"class":109,"line":123},3,[107,125,126],{"class":113},"# exit on error\n",[107,128,130,134],{"class":109,"line":129},4,[107,131,133],{"class":132},"sCcAr","set",[107,135,136],{"class":132}," -e\n",[107,138,140],{"class":109,"line":139},5,[107,141,120],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":52},[107,143,145],{"class":109,"line":144},6,[107,146,147],{"class":113},"# build\n",[107,149,151,155,159],{"class":109,"line":150},7,[107,152,154],{"class":153},"s_sBn","npm",[107,156,158],{"class":157},"sTRMh"," run",[107,160,161],{"class":157}," build\n",[107,163,165],{"class":109,"line":164},8,[107,166,120],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":52},[107,168,170],{"class":109,"line":169},9,[107,171,172],{"class":113},"# move into the build folder — adjust if you changed the output dir\n",[107,174,176,179],{"class":109,"line":175},10,[107,177,178],{"class":132},"cd",[107,180,181],{"class":157}," dist\n",[107,183,185],{"class":109,"line":184},11,[107,186,120],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":52},[107,188,190],{"class":109,"line":189},12,[107,191,192],{"class":113},"# deploy to a custom domain\n",[107,194,196],{"class":109,"line":195},13,[107,197,198],{"class":113},"# echo 'www.example.com' > CNAME\n",[107,200,202],{"class":109,"line":201},14,[107,203,120],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":52},[107,205,207,210],{"class":109,"line":206},15,[107,208,209],{"class":153},"git",[107,211,212],{"class":157}," init\n",[107,214,216,218,221],{"class":109,"line":215},16,[107,217,209],{"class":153},[107,219,220],{"class":157}," add",[107,222,223],{"class":132}," -A\n",[107,225,227,229,232,235],{"class":109,"line":226},17,[107,228,209],{"class":153},[107,230,231],{"class":157}," commit",[107,233,234],{"class":132}," -m",[107,236,237],{"class":157}," 'deploy'\n",[107,239,241],{"class":109,"line":240},18,[107,242,120],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":52},[107,244,246],{"class":109,"line":245},19,[107,247,248],{"class":113},"# deploy to https:\u002F\u002F\u003CUSERNAME>.github.io\n",[107,250,252],{"class":109,"line":251},20,[107,253,254],{"class":113},"# git push -f git@github.com:\u003CUSERNAME>\u002F\u003CUSERNAME>.github.io.git master\n",[107,256,258],{"class":109,"line":257},21,[107,259,120],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":52},[107,261,263],{"class":109,"line":262},22,[107,264,265],{"class":113},"# deploy to https:\u002F\u002F\u003CUSERNAME>.github.io\u002F\u003CREPO>\n",[107,267,269],{"class":109,"line":268},23,[107,270,271],{"class":113},"# git push -f git@github.com:\u003CUSERNAME>\u002F\u003CREPO>.git master:gh-pages\n",[107,273,275],{"class":109,"line":274},24,[107,276,277],{"class":113},"# for this project, change to the line below — this is the SSH version\n",[107,279,281,283,286,289,292],{"class":109,"line":280},25,[107,282,209],{"class":153},[107,284,285],{"class":157}," push",[107,287,288],{"class":132}," -f",[107,290,291],{"class":157}," git@github.com:hsiangfeng\u002FHexfootMusic.git",[107,293,294],{"class":157}," master:gh-pages\n",[107,296,298],{"class":109,"line":297},26,[107,299,300],{"class":113},"# you could also use HTTPS\n",[107,302,304],{"class":109,"line":303},27,[107,305,306],{"class":113},"# git push -f https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002FHexfootMusic.git master:gh-pages\n",[107,308,310],{"class":109,"line":309},28,[107,311,120],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":52},[107,313,315,317],{"class":109,"line":314},29,[107,316,178],{"class":132},[107,318,319],{"class":157}," -\n",[17,321,322],{},"Then in your terminal run:\n(ps. Windows users need to run this through Git Bash — the tool that ships with Git.)",[98,324,328],{"className":325,"code":326,"language":327,"meta":103,"style":103},"language-cmd shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","sh deploy.sh\n","cmd",[61,329,330],{"__ignoreMap":103},[107,331,332],{"class":109,"line":110},[107,333,326],{},[17,335,336],{},"You'll see something magical happen — it automatically builds and deploys to GitHub Pages.",[17,338,339],{},[340,341],"img",{"alt":342,"src":343},"sh deploy.sh","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-02-14%2009.05.24.png",[17,345,346,347,352],{},"This actually comes straight from the official Vue CLI docs — I just never bothered to read ",[28,348,351],{"href":349,"rel":350},"https:\u002F\u002Fcli.vuejs.org\u002Fzh\u002Fguide\u002Fdeployment.html#%E9%80%9A%E7%94%A8%E6%8C%87%E5%8D%97",[32],"them"," carefully (deserves a slap).",[17,354,355],{},"The official Vue CLI docs also cover a bunch of other deployment options, so I'll leave those for you to explore.",[17,357,358],{},[340,359],{"alt":360,"src":361},"Other deployment options","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-02-14%2009.10.24.png",[12,363,365],{"id":364},"what-is-sh","What is sh?",[17,367,368,370],{},[61,369,102],{}," is a script file in Linux. The full name is \"shell\" — a manager that lets users run various tasks. You can kind of think of it like Gulp — a task runner. It's really handy for running a sequence of commands.",[12,372,374],{"id":373},"notes-for-windows","Notes for Windows",[17,376,377,378,380,381,383],{},"Since ",[61,379,102],{}," runs natively on Linux, Mac users can run ",[61,382,342],{}," directly. On Windows you need Git Bash — the tool that comes with Git.",[17,385,386],{},[340,387],{"alt":388,"src":389},"Source: Git official site","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FVue\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-07-29%2009.47.50.png",[12,391,393],{"id":392},"a-lazier-version","A lazier version",[17,395,396,397,399],{},"The script above still needs you to manually pick which transport mode to use (SSH\u002FHTTPS), which is a bit of a pain. And what if your repo moves? You'd have to keep editing ",[61,398,95],{}," every time — totally not the \"one-command deploy\" experience.",[17,401,402],{},"So I wrote a lazier version that figures out the remote repo URL on its own — that's more like it (shrug).",[17,404,405,406,409,410,413],{},"Before you use it though, the project needs to have been through ",[61,407,408],{},"git clone"," or ",[61,411,412],{},"git remote add origin [remote repo URL]"," at least once. Otherwise it errors out because there's no remote URL to grab.",[17,415,416,417,89],{},"The script below auto-detects which transport mode (SSH\u002FHTTPS) to use, so all you have to type is ",[61,418,342],{},[98,420,422],{"className":100,"code":421,"language":102,"meta":103,"style":103},"# exit on error\nset -e\n\n# get the current project's remote URL\noriginUrl=$(git config --get remote.origin.url)\n\n# if the URL looks like this, it's SSH:\n# git@github.com:hsiangfeng\u002FHexfootMusic.git\n# if it looks like this, it's HTTPS:\n# https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002FHexfootMusic.git\n# SSH may run into GitHub Public Keys errors — usually a quick Google fixes it.\n\nnowStatus=${originUrl:0:5}\necho $nowStatus\nif [ $nowStatus = 'https' ]\nthen\n  echo 'Using HTTPS transport'\n  echo 'Current remote URL: '$originUrl\nelse\n  echo 'Using SSH transport'\n  echo 'Current remote URL: '$originUrl\nfi\n\n# build\nnpm run build\n\necho 'Moving into the dist build folder'\n# move into the build folder — adjust if you changed the output dir\ncd dist\n# init and configure git\ngit init\ngit add .\ngit commit -m \"update `date +'%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'`\";\n\n# push to gh-pages\n# SSH might be tricky to configure\ngit push -f $originUrl master:gh-pages\n\ncd -\n",[61,423,424,428,434,438,443,470,474,479,484,489,494,499,503,523,531,547,552,560,570,575,582,590,595,599,603,611,615,622,626,632,638,645,655,676,681,687,693,708,713],{"__ignoreMap":103},[107,425,426],{"class":109,"line":110},[107,427,126],{"class":113},[107,429,430,432],{"class":109,"line":117},[107,431,133],{"class":132},[107,433,136],{"class":132},[107,435,436],{"class":109,"line":123},[107,437,120],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":52},[107,439,440],{"class":109,"line":129},[107,441,442],{"class":113},"# get the current project's remote URL\n",[107,444,445,449,453,456,458,461,464,467],{"class":109,"line":139},[107,446,448],{"class":447},"sMAXC","originUrl",[107,450,452],{"class":451},"sWyjQ","=",[107,454,455],{"class":447},"$(",[107,457,209],{"class":153},[107,459,460],{"class":157}," config",[107,462,463],{"class":132}," --get",[107,465,466],{"class":157}," remote.origin.url",[107,468,469],{"class":447},")\n",[107,471,472],{"class":109,"line":144},[107,473,120],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":52},[107,475,476],{"class":109,"line":150},[107,477,478],{"class":113},"# if the URL looks like this, it's SSH:\n",[107,480,481],{"class":109,"line":164},[107,482,483],{"class":113},"# git@github.com:hsiangfeng\u002FHexfootMusic.git\n",[107,485,486],{"class":109,"line":169},[107,487,488],{"class":113},"# if it looks like this, it's HTTPS:\n",[107,490,491],{"class":109,"line":175},[107,492,493],{"class":113},"# https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002FHexfootMusic.git\n",[107,495,496],{"class":109,"line":184},[107,497,498],{"class":113},"# SSH may run into GitHub Public Keys errors — usually a quick Google fixes it.\n",[107,500,501],{"class":109,"line":189},[107,502,120],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":52},[107,504,505,508,510,513,516,518,520],{"class":109,"line":195},[107,506,507],{"class":447},"nowStatus",[107,509,452],{"class":451},[107,511,512],{"class":447},"${originUrl",[107,514,515],{"class":451},":",[107,517,50],{"class":447},[107,519,515],{"class":451},[107,521,522],{"class":447},"5}\n",[107,524,525,528],{"class":109,"line":201},[107,526,527],{"class":132},"echo",[107,529,530],{"class":447}," $nowStatus\n",[107,532,533,536,539,541,544],{"class":109,"line":206},[107,534,535],{"class":451},"if",[107,537,538],{"class":447}," [ $nowStatus ",[107,540,452],{"class":451},[107,542,543],{"class":157}," 'https'",[107,545,546],{"class":447}," ]\n",[107,548,549],{"class":109,"line":215},[107,550,551],{"class":451},"then\n",[107,553,554,557],{"class":109,"line":226},[107,555,556],{"class":132},"  echo",[107,558,559],{"class":157}," 'Using HTTPS transport'\n",[107,561,562,564,567],{"class":109,"line":240},[107,563,556],{"class":132},[107,565,566],{"class":157}," 'Current remote URL: '",[107,568,569],{"class":447},"$originUrl\n",[107,571,572],{"class":109,"line":245},[107,573,574],{"class":451},"else\n",[107,576,577,579],{"class":109,"line":251},[107,578,556],{"class":132},[107,580,581],{"class":157}," 'Using SSH transport'\n",[107,583,584,586,588],{"class":109,"line":257},[107,585,556],{"class":132},[107,587,566],{"class":157},[107,589,569],{"class":447},[107,591,592],{"class":109,"line":262},[107,593,594],{"class":451},"fi\n",[107,596,597],{"class":109,"line":268},[107,598,120],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":52},[107,600,601],{"class":109,"line":274},[107,602,147],{"class":113},[107,604,605,607,609],{"class":109,"line":280},[107,606,154],{"class":153},[107,608,158],{"class":157},[107,610,161],{"class":157},[107,612,613],{"class":109,"line":297},[107,614,120],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":52},[107,616,617,619],{"class":109,"line":303},[107,618,527],{"class":132},[107,620,621],{"class":157}," 'Moving into the dist build folder'\n",[107,623,624],{"class":109,"line":309},[107,625,172],{"class":113},[107,627,628,630],{"class":109,"line":314},[107,629,178],{"class":132},[107,631,181],{"class":157},[107,633,635],{"class":109,"line":634},30,[107,636,637],{"class":113},"# init and configure git\n",[107,639,641,643],{"class":109,"line":640},31,[107,642,209],{"class":153},[107,644,212],{"class":157},[107,646,648,650,652],{"class":109,"line":647},32,[107,649,209],{"class":153},[107,651,220],{"class":157},[107,653,654],{"class":157}," .\n",[107,656,658,660,662,664,667,670,673],{"class":109,"line":657},33,[107,659,209],{"class":153},[107,661,231],{"class":157},[107,663,234],{"class":132},[107,665,666],{"class":157}," \"update `",[107,668,669],{"class":153},"date",[107,671,672],{"class":157}," +'%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'`\"",[107,674,675],{"class":447},";\n",[107,677,679],{"class":109,"line":678},34,[107,680,120],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":52},[107,682,684],{"class":109,"line":683},35,[107,685,686],{"class":113},"# push to gh-pages\n",[107,688,690],{"class":109,"line":689},36,[107,691,692],{"class":113},"# SSH might be tricky to configure\n",[107,694,696,698,700,702,705],{"class":109,"line":695},37,[107,697,209],{"class":153},[107,699,285],{"class":157},[107,701,288],{"class":132},[107,703,704],{"class":447}," $originUrl ",[107,706,707],{"class":157},"master:gh-pages\n",[107,709,711],{"class":109,"line":710},38,[107,712,120],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":52},[107,714,716,718],{"class":109,"line":715},39,[107,717,178],{"class":132},[107,719,319],{"class":157},[17,721,722],{},[340,723],{"alt":724,"src":725},"Lazy version","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FHexo\u002F%E8%A9%A6%E8%91%97%E5%AD%B8%20Hexo%20%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-08-04%2013.04.09.png",[17,727,728,729,732,733,736],{},"One last thing — for the \"lazy version\" to work, I recommend you've already run ",[61,730,731],{},"git push"," at least once and confirmed your machine can ",[86,734,735],{},"successfully push code to GitHub",". If you haven't, do that first.",[17,738,739],{},"Otherwise you'll likely run into auth\u002Fpermission errors, and you'll have to Google your way out.",[12,741,743],{"id":742},"polished-and-enhanced-lazy-version","Polished and enhanced lazy version",[17,745,746],{},"Below is the polished, enhanced version of the lazy script. The main goal is making the workflow easier to follow, plus it adds a few extras:",[748,749,750,776,787,798,816,824],"ul",{},[751,752,753,754,757],"li",{},"Auto-creates ",[61,755,756],{},"vue.config.js",[748,758,759,765],{},[751,760,761,762,764],{},"Detects whether ",[61,763,756],{}," exists and creates one with the right content if not. This only runs once.",[751,766,767,768,771,772,775],{},"Only writes ",[61,769,770],{},".\u002F"," for ",[61,773,774],{},"publicPath"," — see the inline comments for details.",[751,777,778,779],{},"Detects the OS (mainly Mac vs Windows)\n",[748,780,781],{},[751,782,783],{},[784,785,786],"del",{},"Mostly because color codes glitch on Windows, hence the detection",[751,788,789,790],{},"Auto-builds the Vue CLI app\n",[748,791,792],{},[751,793,794,795,797],{},"You don't have to type ",[61,796,63],{},"; the script handles it.",[751,799,800,801],{},"Auto-detects the GitHub remote URL and stages changes\n",[748,802,803],{},[751,804,805,806,808,809,815],{},"After building, it auto-adds ",[61,807,67],{}," to version control and pulls your current remote branch. As above, make sure you've ",[86,810,811,812,814],{},"run ",[61,813,731],{}," at least once"," for the source repo, or this is likely to fail.",[751,817,818,819],{},"Auto-deploys Vue CLI to GitHub Pages\n",[748,820,821],{},[751,822,823],{},"After build it auto-deploys to GitHub Pages and pushes to the branch.",[751,825,826],{},[784,827,828],{},"Pretty terminal output",[17,830,831],{},"Here are the download links:",[748,833,834,841,848],{},[751,835,836],{},[28,837,840],{"href":838,"rel":839},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002FvueDeploySH",[32],"GitHub repo",[751,842,843],{},[28,844,847],{"href":845,"rel":846},"https:\u002F\u002Fraw.githubusercontent.com\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002FvueDeploySH\u002Fmaster\u002Fdeploy.sh",[32],"vueDeploySH script page",[751,849,850],{},[28,851,854],{"href":852,"rel":853},"https:\u002F\u0